x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.125, p.641 (1969)

x4freetext: FIRST VERSION OF DATA.
SECOND VERSION OF DATA.
-ELASTIC AND INELASTIC SCATTERING OF FAST NEUTRONS
FROM IRON, NICKEL AND TUNGSTEN-
5.5 MV PULSED BEAM VAN DE GRAAFF ACCELERATOR
WITH MOBLEY-TYPE BEAM BUNCHER.
T(P,N)HE-3.
TIME-OF-FLIGHT.
.DATA ANALYSED USING OPTICAL-MODEL, HAUSER-FESHBACH
AND MOLDAUER THEORIES. BEST-FIT SETS OF OPTICAL-MODEL
PARAMETERS GIVEN IN REFERENCE.
.DATA FROM PRIV. COMM., K.TSUKADA. SOME OF
THE DATA RECEIVED MAY 1967 (1-ST VERSION)
HAVE BEEN REPLACED BY THE 2-ND VERSION
RECEIVED MARCH 1968.
A.P.T. JAPAN CODE CHANGED TO JPN
.CORRECTIONS FOR MULTIPLE SCATTERING, NEUTRON-FLUX
ATTENUATION, SOURCE-TO-SAMPLE GEOMETRICAL EFFECTS IN
THE SCATTERING SAMPLES AND POLYETHYLENE BY THE MONTE-
CARLO PROGRAM MULT1.
.ERRORS INDICATED CONTAIN STATISTICAL ERRORS AND ERRORS
ORIGINATING IN THE PEELING-OFF PROCEDURE WHEN IT IS
APPLIED.
